
"Happy New Year's Olivia." he spoke softly.
We both leaned in this time and our lips meet, just in time. Our soft lips smashed together as one. We molded our body together, no space in between. The spark was noticeable, this was meant to happen.
I lean back for a breath and looked into his green eyes. We went in for a more eager. This could last forever.
Author's Note:
Love is blind.